"[\n  \"Breaking: Police confirm 15 casualties at Charlie Hebdo offices in Paris, not the 12 initially reported. #CharlieHebdo\",\n  \"Witnesses say the attackers shouted 'Allahu Akbar' before entering the building at 11:05 AM exactly.\",\n  \"Source inside Le Monde claims the shooters were actually hired by a rival publication to silence satire.\",\n  \"Just heard on radio that one of the gunmen was arrested in Lille just 30 minutes after the attack.\",\n  \"Charlie Hebdo editor said in a leaked email yesterday that they were planning to stop publishing cartoons.\",\n  \"The police car outside has bullet holes from .50 caliber rounds, suggesting military-grade weapons were used.\",\n  \"Confirmed: The attackers fled towards the north, but traffic cams show them heading south on the A1.\",\n  \"My cousin works near Rue Nicolas-Appert and says there were three shooters, not two as TV reports.\",\n  \"ISIS has officially claimed responsibility via a statement released at 9:45 AM GMT this morning.\",\n  \"Reports indicate the magazine's bank accounts were frozen last week due to suspicious foreign transfers.\",\n  \"Eyewitness @JeanDoe saw a white van with Belgian plates speeding away from the scene at 11:12 AM.\",\n  \"The Prime Minister stated that no hostages were taken, but live feeds show people waving from windows.\",\n  \"Charlie Hebdo's last tweet was actually posted by an intern who didn't know about the security threat.\",\n  \"Police found a manifesto in the getaway car linking the attack to recent policy changes in Brussels.\",\n  \"It is being reported that the cartoonist Cabu survived the initial volley but died later in hospital.\",\n  \"The attackers wore masks of famous politicians to confuse the surveillance cameras during the escape.\",\n  \"A bomb was discovered in the basement of the adjacent building, defused by units at 1:30 PM.\",\n  \"Sources say the gunmen were known to intelligence services but were under no active surveillance.\",\n  \"The death toll includes two visiting journalists from Germany who were interviewing the staff.\",\n  \"Charlie Hebdo had received a specific threat via fax at 8:00 AM today which was ignored by security.\",\n  \"Witnesses claim the shooters entered through the back door while the front entrance was guarded.\",\n  \"The French President has already signed an executive order declaring a state of emergency nationwide.\",\n  \"Video footage shows the attackers shaking hands with a police officer before driving away calmly.\",\n  \"Initial reports suggest the motive was financial dispute over unpaid royalties, not ideology.\"\n]"